trend_summary: Across the time-series, the territory remained a green, golf-course-anchored suburb, but steady infill replaced scattered woodland pockets with housing and small commercial plazas. Road corridors widened, especially the north freeway interchange, and parking expanses enlarged. Overall fabric shifted from leafy sprawl toward closer-packed lots without reaching true urban density.
notable_changes: Progressive infill housing east and south of the central golf course, replacing tree cover.
Emergence of new retail/office blocks in the south-west industrial strip.
Widening and realignment of the northern freeway interchange with added ramps.
Incremental loss of scattered forest patches in the north-east to new subdivisions.
